  <bioghist id="aspace_ed343b0c4dae4fa5ac2d1bc0aa0d281f">
    <head>ORGANIZATIONAL HISTORY</head>
<p>The New York State College of Veterinary Medicine was founded in 1894.The College was opened for classes in 1896. The faculty has had regular meetings since this date.</p>  </bioghist>
  <relatedmaterial id="aspace_ff5004432d826049c40347834e9244c0">
    <head>RELATED MATERIAL</head>
<p>Another set of faculty minutes is housed in the <extref xlink:href="http://www.vet.cornell.edu/library/" xlink:show="new"> Flower-Sprecher Veterinary Library</extref>. Access to that collection is also restricted to faculty of the College of Veterinary Medicine.</p>  </relatedmaterial>
  <arrangement id="aspace_002bd83d0224963bf84b65744d687ba5">
    <head>COLLECTION ARRANGEMENT</head>
<p>Chronological.</p>  </arrangement>
  <prefercite id="aspace_a2e3d2a54d53c2d0c07ac3e459a09967">
    <head>Cite As:</head>
<p>New York State College of Veterinary Medicine Faculty Minutes, # 24-02-1672. Division of Rare and Manuscript Collections, Cornell University Library.</p>  </prefercite>
  <scopecontent audience="internal" id="aspace_2a9d55a679eb47e4fc08921dbff98fab">
    <head>Scope and content</head>
<p>Minutes of faculty meetings of the New York State College of Veterinary Medicine at Cornell University, 1896-1985. An index for 1964-1972 is included. Also minutes from 2005-2007 and 2008-2009 (2 volumes).</p>  </scopecontent>
  <accessrestrict audience="internal" id="aspace_83593350e1c3c0af2e2105e750d65509">
    <head>Access Restrictions:</head>
<p>Access restricted to faculty of the College of Veterinary Medicine.</p>  </accessrestrict>
